Name: Tom Kingston
Comment: In general software engineers usually don’t do anything with machine learning. Machine learning leans very heavily into data science. There are sub groups of software engineers such as machine learning engineers who write libraries which data scientists use. But to get in that field requires a lot of study and schooling. Not only do you have to know how to write software but also have to have a solid foundation in data science.

Comment: It would be very beneficial for beginners to make Shallow, Deep and Convolutional Neural Networks from scratch. Later on, they can shift to Tensorflow or Scikit when doing professional learning but I do advise to at least implement a neural network from scratch.
